description: TEHRAN – Following Britain’s sanctions against three Iranian individuals and an institution under the pretext of causing instability in the West Asia region, the Iranian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday summoned the British charge d’affairs to declare the Islamic Republic’s protest to the move.
title: Foreign Ministry summons British diplomat over anti-Iran sanctions

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has expressed his government’s unwavering support for the struggles of all the oppressed nations across the world, particularly the Palestinian resistance against the occupation regime of Israel.
title: Pezeshkian expresses unwavering support for Palestinians’ campaign against occupation

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has expressed his government’s unwavering support for the struggles of all the oppressed nations across the world, particularly the Palestinian resistance against the occupation regime of Israel.
title: Pezeshkian expresses unwavering support for Palestinians’ struggle for justice

description: TEHRAN – Iran found their bearings late in the third quarter and went on to roll past a hard-fighting India side, 70-53, to move one win away from a clean sweep of Group B in the FIBA U18 Asia Cup 2024, Tuesday at the Arena Complex.
title: Iran victorious over India at 2024 FIBA U18 Asia Cup

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday summoned Canberra’s ambassador to Tehran to strongly protest the posting an offensive content on the Australian embassy’s official Instagram page a day earlier.
title: Iran summons Australian envoy over offensive content

description: TEHRAN - Writing an article in the Jerusalem Strategic Tribune, Richard Nephew, the architect of sanctions against Iran during the Obama administration, says sanctions on Iran are “harder than it seems”, especially as the situation has changed in the world.
title: Sanctions on Iran harder than it seems: Richard Nephew

description: PARIS – Iran’s men’s sitting volleyball team defeated Germany in straight sets (25-16, 25-13, 25-16) on Tuesday to advance to the semifinals of the 2024 Paralympic Games.
title: Iran sitting volleyball into 2024 Paralympics semis

description: PARIS - Hajar Safarzadeh of Iran made history in the women’s 400 meters T12, winning a silver medal of the 20924 Paralympic Games.
title: Female sprinter Safarzadeh makes history in 2024 Paralympic Games

description: TEHRAN - Roberto Piazza took charge of Iran national volleyball team until 2028 Olympic Games to be held in Los Angeles, the U.S.
title: Roberto Piazza appointed Iran volleyball coach till 2028
